From 8064621a862e8332cc4e530f4313561307a5d051 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 23:53:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Edition-aware SKSE, manifest load order/separators, and
 launch lockdown

Bug fixes:
- SKSE is now installed per game edition. The compiler no longer bakes the
  (edition-specific) skse64 loader/runtime into the manifest; instead the
  launcher detects Steam vs GOG from the game copy and downloads the matching
  SKSE build, copying the loader/DLLs to the game root and the scripts into a
  managed MO2 mod. SKSE is not part of the client-files bundle, so this is the
  only place it gets installed.
- The compiler now captures the full modlist order including separators and the
  plugins.txt load order; the installer recreates separator folders, writes the
  captured plugin order, and preserves any user-added mods in modlist.txt.

UI:
- 'Open & Configure MO2' disables itself and shows 'MO2 is running' plus a
  'Warning: MO2 takes a moment to start up.' note on click.
- Game-copy progress now also feeds the modpack install status field and
  updates on every chunk so long copies no longer look frozen.

Launch lockdown:
- On MO2 launch, disable any user-added mod that ships a plugin (esp/esm/esl)
  or an SKSE plugin DLL, so only the server modpack can load. Launcher-installed
  mods (marked skyrpManaged) and separators are kept; texture/mesh-only mods the
  player added stay enabled. Plugin load order is enforced from the server.

